                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>ITEM Z103—RABBI SEEKS POSITION, <date>1851</date>. Neatly penned single sheet<lb/>\n                letter (blank reverse) 7 ½ x 8. <placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>August 26, 1851</date> entirely in the<lb/> hand of and signed by “<persName\n                    role=\"author\">D. Lilienthall</persName>” to <persName>Rev. Leeser</persName>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> “...allow me to introduce to you\n                    <persName>Dr. Zimerman</persName> (sic) a man well instructed<lb/> and who would\n                like to get a situation as teacher. If you could help him to<lb/> a place you would\n                oblige me very much and I would be very happy if he<lb/> could find a situation like\n                that of <persName>Dr. Scwess</persName>, who after having been sometime in\n                    <placeName>Phila</placeName><lb/> got such a pleasant situation. Do for him what\n                you can, he is without nay means<lb/> whatever.” Lightest aging. Exc. Small tatters\n                on the extreme edge of bottom blank margin<lb/> only. Reverse acts as cover with\n                address to <persName>Leeser</persName>...</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">______________________</p>\n            <p>2 of 13</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><date>1<lb/>15<lb/>02</date> 8:07 PM</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3j46m/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
